<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><rss version="2.0"><channel><title>Conteúdo de fisl12 marcado com a tag "sl radio"</title><link>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12</link><description>Conteúdo de fisl12 marcado com a tag "sl radio"</description><item><title>Journalism undergraduates will be able to cover fisl12</title><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;Working as a volunteer in the largest free software event in Latin America may be a great opportunity for professionals willing to join the workmarket or for those who wish to gather knowledge. Besides enriching their resumé, the media coverage of the event allows students to really feel the daily pressure of a real press room. fisl's communication team is in charge of writing stories for the website, interview for the Free Software Radio and report for the Free Software TV.&lt;br&gt;Inside the fisl fair, a press-room booth is assembled, where the plots are are discussed, produced and edited. Volunteers colaborate in the whole process, concluding with the publication of the video in TVSL website, the podcast in the SL Radio website, or the text in fisl's website. This year, for the first time, a team of volunteers will do media coverage for fisl's website, which last year reached 2 million page views. Audience in the TV and Radio were also  expressive: only during the event the Radio had 693 unique listeners and the two websites had almost 80.000 visits in the four days.&lt;br&gt;Gabriel Galli, 6º semester journalism student at PUCRS is a veteran in fisl coverage. He volunteered in the last two editions and is preparing for his third. "Work at fisl is very enriching, both to the point of view of communication and of the free software, an opportunity to get in contact with the greatest figures in the subject and also to learn how to use software", he says.&lt;br&gt;Those who are interested in volunteering in media coverage of fisl12 may write to voluntariosfisl12 AT softwarelivre DOT org &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;img src="/articles/0032/0542/cartaz-site.jpg1305317533" height="670" alt="Cartaz_site" width="474"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 13 May 2011 17:25:18 +0000</pubDate><link>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12/fisl12/noticias/journalism-undergraduates-will-be-able-to-cover-fisl12</link><guid>http://softwarelivre.org/fisl12/fisl12/noticias/journalism-undergraduates-will-be-able-to-cover-fisl12</guid></item></channel></rss>